HEADWORD: Leptus
<hw>Lep"tus</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧p"t⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>lepto`s</grk> thin, small.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The six-legged young, or larva, of certain
mites; -- sometimes used as a generic name. See <cref>Harvest
mite</cref>, under <er>Harvest</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leptynite</ent>⟦br⟧
